Input Layer: Receives input data related to emotions and emotional responses from the user interface or other sources.

Output Layer: Delivers output related to emotions and emotional responses to the MASTER NEURAL NETWORK.

Functionality: This neural network models the amygdala region of the brain, which is responsible for processing emotions and emotional responses. Its functionality will include processes such as identifying emotions, processing emotional cues, and generating appropriate emotional responses.

Connection to MASTER NEURAL NETWORK: The Amygdala Neural Network will connect to the MASTER NEURAL NETWORK via a bidirectional communication channel, allowing for efficient information flow.
